keyValuePair.Value: Can you kick off with a win?
It's exciting for everybody, for the fans and for yourselves: the start of your %1s campaign. How are you feeling? Confident you can kick off with a win?
We'll have to see how we match up.
This game's too close to call. Both teams look strong. Both clubs are ambitious. The opposition will be as desperate for the win as we are today.
We can't wait!
You can feel the anticipation around the club. In our dressing room, too. We've been looking forward to getting our campaign off to the best possible start.
We'll have to stay calm.
In opening fixtures like this, form doesn't count for much. Anything could happen. We'll have to stay focused the whole 90 minutes to avoid any surprises.
A great start. Can you grab another win?
Your %1s campaign go off to the best possible start. I'm sure your boys are feeling confident. Can you make it two wins from two now?
It's another game.
What happened in our opening game probably won't have much bearing on what happens here. If we're going to win again, we'll have to stay calm and take our chances.
I'm feeling very positive.
I saw a lot of good things from us in our opening win. If we play to that standard again here, I'm confident we can get another win and all but guarantee we'll get out of the group.
We're enjoying the pressure.
Of course there's expectation on the boys' shoulders. But this is a strong-minded group of players. I know we can handle the pressure that comes with games in this competition.
Can you get a first group stage win?
It wasn't the start you were hoping for in your %1s group, but there's plenty of time to recover from that defeat. Are you confident your team can get the win they need today?
Every game's difficult, isn't it?
We were disappointed to lose our first game. And this next one won't be any easier. But we've trained well and we're ready to go out and win today.
We've got to improve on that first game.
We've got an experienced group of players here and I expect much more from them. That was a bad defeat and we can't afford to drop more points today.
We're just focused on this game.
Looking back at that defeat won't help us now. We've got to be positive. We've got to go out and get the win that'll put us back on track in the group.
Can we look forward to another victory?
It's been the best possible start. Another win today would put you well on course for the %1s knock-out stages. Can your boys make it three in a row?
We won't take this game for granted.
Yes, we've made an excellent start. But those two wins won't make this game any easier. We're up against a very good side and I can see it going either way, to be honest.
We're in top form right now.
I'm delighted with how the team's been playing. Delighted with our results, too. We'll go out and play our football again today. I really do think we're good enough to win this group.
The lads have a great attitude.
I can't fault the way my players have been preparing for these group games. They're determined and humble. They know each game can be a real challenge. Let's see what happens today.
Can you get the win you need?
It looks like a second win in the group should see you through to the knock-out stages of this season's %1s. Are you confident your boys can pick up a positive result?
We're ready for the challenge.
We already know there are no easy games in this group. Today will be no different, but with hard work and the right attitude, we've got every chance of getting the win we need
We'll do everything we can.
This is a very challenging group and we know it won't be easy today. All we can do is try to be at our very best and hope that'll be good enough.
We should already be through.
I think the boys have let themselves down a bit. We should already have got the points we need but, as it is, we've still got work to do. Qualifying is our absolute minimum target.
Can your boys keep your dreams alive?
You've not won a group game so far and the %1s knock-out stages look a very long way off. Can the team get the win you need to keep your qualification hopes alive?
We'll make sure we're ready.
All we can do now is go out there in a positive frame of mind and do everything we can to win the game. If we do that but don't get the result, then so be it.
We've under-performed, that's for sure.
We're in this situation for a reason. We've been poor in our first two games. I'd say our chances of qualifying are pretty slim, but I've told the players they have to give it everything today.
We have to forget our position.
If we think too much about the situation we're in, we'll put ourselves under pressure. We can't afford for the boys to freeze. We have to just focus on this game. And on winning it!
